description:
At Capdau School. Series photographs show: Negatives 2 & 3--
Agnes Bulmer (9), 2626 Gladiolus St.; Anel Betty Scheaffer (7), 2621 Jonquil St.; John Joseph Landry, Jr.
(10), 2561 Gladiolus St.; Constance R. Mire (12), 2428 Jasmine St.; Negative 8--Lester Murray (14), 4005
Velie St.; Edward Gatzman (12), 3918 Velie St.; Negative 9-- June Brockett (12), 2638 Lavender
St.

The Louisiana Library Commission sponsors the operation of a
bookmobile manned by WPA workers to furnish books to New Orleans children.

At the Canal branch, New Orleans Public Library. Blind persons who are
unable to read embossed type need no longer be deprived of education and entertainment because the
Library, with the aid of the WPA, has made talking books available to all blind persons in Louisiana.
Interior.
